    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. can you walk me through how the nearest-neighbor approach would actually work in practice? like, if i'm starting at the warehouse, how does the logic decide which stop is next?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The nearest-neighbor logic simply starts at your warehouse and identifies the single drop-off point closest to the current location. It then permanently marks that stop as visited, calculates the distance from there, and immediately repeats the process to find the nearest unvisited point from this new location, creating a step-by-step path. This greedy approach is extremely fast and easy to implement, though it doesn't always guarantee the mathematically shortest total distance compared to more complex algorithms.",
      "source": "target",
